Activity for the Analysis of Distance Based Data

This is an R Markdown Notebook and contains the activities associated with gaining inferences from Distance-based data in landscape genetics.

The Data

For this activity, you will be using the following data. These data are provided online and can be downloaded by executing the code in the following chunk. By default, I set the options on this chunk to eval=FALSE so it does not hit my servers every time you save this document.

data_url <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dyerlab/ENVS-Lectures/master/data/Araptus_Disperal_Bias.csv"
data <- read_csv( data_url)
summary( data )

Data Process 1: {Name}

Necessity: The first thing we need to do is locate and get the data into R from whatever centralized repository1. By default, much of the data we work with should be hosted in ASCII format so that in the future, no matter where you are or who you are collaborating with, you will be able to get these data and use them.

Approach: To accomplish this task, we are going to use the tidyverse and gstudio functions created specifically to import data from external repositories, then check it to make sure there are no errors.

  1. Identify URL for repository
  2. Download as a raw file
  3. Translate over genotypes columns
  4. Check for obvious errors in ploidy, coding, and/or missing data.
